
Check for the heading whether it shows Authenticated Enrollment or Open Enrolment
1.If Authenticated Enrollment :

click the link Switch to Open Enrollment

If youswitch to  open enrollment: After clicking,
Click the radio of open enrollment
Click learn more link under it : it navigates to https://www.hexnode.com/mobile-device-management/help/enroll-android-mobile-devices-hexnode-mdm/#

In the default user dropdown, search etoe_test. If there, select it. If not there, add button will be there. Click add new user:
Display name : etoe_test
Email: etoe_test@example.com

Click create. 

In Default password  - enter tryhard1!

Click next 
“Enrollment settings successfully updated” message appears

Then it will change to open enrolment

Click Hexnode MDM  link. It navigates to https://www.hexnode.com/mobile-device-management/help/enroll-windows-mobile-devices-hexnode-mdm/#no-auth

In the Default email - click change
a dialog opens
In Change user :  click and select the first value.
click done
Enrollment settings successfully updated message will come and Default email - your selected email will be visible

In the password - click change
In the New password field: enter Tryhard01!
click done
Enrollment settings successfully updated message appears and the password will be masked. click the eye icon and check whether the updated password is visible



Click send mail - “Enrollment request successfully created” message appears
Click send sms - a dialog opens and asks for phone number. Give 123456789
Click send - “Enrollment request successfully created” message appears

There will be a message like : Note: All the devices will be assigned to the user etoe_test change.
Click change.
Click domain and select second value
Change user and select first value
Now the message will be changed to Note: All the devices will be assigned to the user <selected user’s name> change


Then in the page with heading shows Open Enrollment :

click the link switch to authenticated enrollment
Check the radio for  Authenticated Enrollment
Click learn more link under it : it navigates to https://www.hexnode.com/mobile-device-management/help/enroll-windows-mobile-devices-hexnode-mdm/#email-or-sms-enrollment

Under Enrollment Request:
Toggle and toggle back all the checkboxes and finally 
Check Local User and Google user
Under Self Enrollment:
Toggle and toggle back all the checkboxes and finally 
Check Local User and Google user

Under Ownership:
Toggle and toggle back all the radio button and finally choose personal

Click next 
“Enrollment settings successfully updated” message appears
Then it will change to Authenticated enrolment

In the Send enrollment request via : check email
In user dropdown, search etoe_test. If there, select it. If not there, add button will be there. Click add new user:
Display name : etoe_test
Email: etoe_test@example.com

Click create. 

Click send

“Enrollment request successfully created” message comes


In the Send enrollment request via : check sms
In user dropdown, search etoe_test. If there, select it. If not there, add button will be there. Click add new user:
Display name : etoe_test
Email: etoe_test@example.com

Click create. 

Enter Phone no : 123456789

Click send

“Enrollment request successfully created” message comes


In the page there is a message like: Change the SMS settings here - click here link. It opens SMS Settings dialog
Click test sms
In the to - enter 123456789

In message: etoe test
Click send. Error message “Please provide a valid number.” Appears
Enter placeholder value itself
Click send. It shows “Please enter valid account details”
Note down all the values.
Click reset 
Confirmation dialog with message “Configured SMS will be Removed” comes. 
Click yes
“SMS account removed successfully” message appears
You haven't configured an SMS server. Click here to configure one now. - click - click here
Enter the saved details and click save
“SMS account saved successfully” appears

The text Change the SMS settings here appears again

We use the default email server to send emails to the users. You can configure your own server from here - Click here

Server name:etoe test
Port : 1111
Sender email : etoe_test@example.com
Check:
Enable TLS

Enable SSL

Enable Authentication - username : etoe_test
Password: etoetest

Click test email

Enter to email as etoe_test_to@example.com
Click send 
“mail sending failed. please check your port number,authentication” appears

Click cancel
Click save
The message will change to Click here to configure a new email server.

Click - click here
 Dialog with “Email Server Configuration” appears.
Click change password. Enter the same password again
Click save

The dialog closes

